### Shop Network — API examples
### Run with the JetBrains HTTP Client (PhpStorm) or the VS Code REST Client.
### Run top to bottom: the create requests capture ids into variables used by the reads.
### Requires the stack running — `make start` is enough (these requests create their own data).
### Default base http://localhost:8080.

@base = http://localhost:8080

### Create a manager
POST {{base}}/api/managers
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Jane Cooper" }

> {% client.global.set("managerId", response.body.id); %}

### Create a shop (Paris Marais)
POST {{base}}/api/shops
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Paris Marais",
  "address": "12 rue de Rivoli, 75004 Paris",
  "latitude": 48.8559,
  "longitude": 2.3601,
  "managerId": "{{managerId}}"
}

> {% client.global.set("shopId", response.body.id); %}

### Create a product (in stock below)
POST {{base}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Wrap dress", "pictureUrl": "https://example.com/wrap-dress.jpg" }

> {% client.global.set("productId", response.body.id); %}

### Set this product's stock in the shop
PUT {{base}}/api/products/{{productId}}/stock
Content-Type: application/json

[ { "shopId": "{{shopId}}", "quantity": 12 } ]

### List the catalog (search by name, sorted, paginated)
GET {{base}}/api/products?search=dress&sort=name&direction=asc&page=1&limit=20

### Search shops near Paris (geolocation)
GET {{base}}/api/shops?lat=48.8566&lng=2.3522&radius=5000&page=1&limit=20

### Stock of the shop (out-of-stock excluded by default)
GET {{base}}/api/stock?shopIds={{shopId}}

### Products of the shop (shop as a resource — 404 if unknown)
GET {{base}}/api/shops/{{shopId}}/products

### Availability of the product near Paris
GET {{base}}/api/products/{{productId}}/availability?lat=48.8566&lng=2.3522&radius=5000
